A GOOD-NIGHT<br/><br/>CLOSE now thine eyes and rest secure; 
<br />Thy soul is safe enough, thy body sure; 
<br />He that loves thee, He that keeps 
<br />And guards thee, never slumbers, never sleeps.
<br /><br />The smiling conscience in a sleeping breast 
<br />Has only peace, has only rest; 
<br />The music and the mirth of kings 
<br />Are all but very discords, when she sings; 
<br />Then close thine eyes and rest secure; 
<br />No sleep so sweet as thine, no rest so sure. 
